---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const title = 'Privacy Policy â€” ByteWorks';
const description = 'ByteWorks respects your privacy. Learn how we handle, store, and protect your data.';
---

<Base title={title} description={description} image="/og-image.svg" lang="en">
  <section class="px-6 md:px-10 lg:px-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto py-14 md:py-20 space-y-8">
    <header class="text-center mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mt-2">Effective as of October 2025</p>
    </header>

    <article class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-200 text-sm md:text-base leading-relaxed">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          ByteWorks ("we", "our", "us") respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal data. This policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you interact with our website or services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We may collect personal data that you voluntarily provide, such as:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Name and contact information (email, phone number).</li>
          <li>Messages or details submitted through contact or quote forms.</li>
          <li>Technical data such as IP address, browser type, and device information (collected automatically through analytics tools).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">3. Use of Google Services and Integrations</h2>
        <p>
          We use integrations with Google services (such as Google Sheets, Google Analytics, and Google Business) to process form submissions, analyze site traffic, and improve performance. These services may store or process limited user data according to Google's Privacy Policy:
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400 underline">https://policies.google.com/privacy</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">4. Contact Form Data Handling</h2>
        <p>
          Information submitted through our contact or quote forms is used solely to respond to your request, provide a quotation, or deliver the requested service. All data is securely stored and deleted upon request or within 12 months of inactivity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">5. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may use cookies or similar technologies to improve user experience and understand visitor behavior. You can disable cookies in your browser settings at any time. Some features may not function properly if cookies are disabled.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">6. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Personal data related to service inquiries or form submissions is retained for up to 12 months, unless deletion is requested earlier. Backups containing limited metadata may be stored securely for operational continuity.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">7. Data Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use SSL encryption, secure hosting, and access controls to protect your data. While no system is completely secure, ByteWorks applies best practices to reduce risk of unauthorized access, loss, or alteration.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">8. Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access, correction, or deletion of your personal data at any time by writing to
          <span class="font-medium">privacy@byteworks.agency</span>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">9. Policy Updates</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy when necessary. The current version will always be available on this page.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </section>
</Base>

